A very naive (but working) realloc, just follow this algorithm:
• Allocate a new bloc of the given size using malloc;
• Copy data from the old one to the new one;
• Free the old block;
• Return the new pointer.
Of course, we want something a little bit more e ﬃcient: we don’t want a new allocation if
we have enough room where we are. The di ﬀerent cases are thus:
